title.narrative: OUTPUT 4.C: CHILD PROTECTION SEVICES

description.narrative: Output 4.3 :A package of quality services and targeted awareness raising is available to prevent and respond to the protection impacts of the most vulnerable conflict affected children, which contributes to Access To Justice, Children With Disabilities, Harmful Practices (Fgm/C And Child Marriage), Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Improved and equitable preventive and responsive services addressing violence, abuse and exploitation of children
